From 054c9d3fb35f0a3cdd81cce8adb8810149847010 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: James Haggerty <james.haggerty@morsemicro.com>
Date: Mon, 16 Dec 2024 13:21:22 +1100
Subject: [PATCH] wifi: mt76: mt7603: force SMPS mode to be set again on
 association

When Dynamic power save was in the HT IE, even though the command was
being sent to the firmware (in the rate table update after the station
was added) it wasn't taking effect: MCS15 was still used without RTS.

Forcing it to set this in the firmware again after association seems
to resolve the issue.
---
 mt7603/main.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/mt7603/main.c b/mt7603/main.c
index 89d738de..ea97f0f2 100644
--- a/mt7603/main.c
+++ b/mt7603/main.c
@@ -373,6 +373,9 @@ mt7603_sta_assoc(struct mt76_dev *mdev, struct ieee80211_vif *vif,
 		 struct ieee80211_sta *sta)
 {
 	struct mt7603_dev *dev = container_of(mdev, struct mt7603_dev, mt76);
+	struct mt7603_sta *msta = (struct mt7603_sta *)sta->drv_priv;
+
+	msta->smps = ~0;
 
 	mt7603_wtbl_update_cap(dev, sta);
 }
-- 
